  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/32015086" />
    <a title="Ron" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1256262-ron"><img alt="Ron" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442983573p2/1256262.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/32015086?book_show_action=true">Sep 04, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ron" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ron" href="/user/show/1256262-ron">Ron</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">students of the Dark Ages</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1256262-ron?shelf=religion-philosophy">religion-philosophy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1256262-ron?shelf=christian_life">christian_life</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer32015086" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6768009671835698195">One of the most influential books of the Middle Ages, bridging the passing of classical culture and rise of Medieval Europe.<br/><br/>Invaluable aid to understanding the worldview of Medieval man. For a scholarly analysis of what and how, refer to C. S. Lewis&apos;s <i>The Discarded Image<i> ISBN 0521477352. <br/><br/>Paradoxically, another complementary text is Thomas Cahill&apos;s <i>How the Irish Saved Civilization,</i> (ISBN 0385418493) covering the same period when Boethius&apos; influence was greatest (though Cahill offers Augustine as </i></i></span>
  <span id="freeText6768009671835698195" style="display:none">One of the most influential books of the Middle Ages, bridging the passing of classical culture and rise of Medieval Europe.<br /><br />Invaluable aid to understanding the worldview of Medieval man. For a scholarly analysis of what and how, refer to C. S. Lewis's <i>The Discarded Image<i> ISBN 0521477352. <br /><br />Paradoxically, another complementary text is Thomas Cahill's <i>How the Irish Saved Civilization,</i> (ISBN 0385418493) covering the same period when Boethius' influence was greatest (though Cahill offers Augustine as the pinnacle (and depth) of the lost culture and Ausunius the Poetas as the weary, wasted remains.)</i></i></span>
